  "prompt": "What countries have extradition treaties with UAE?",
  "response": "As of October 2023, the United Arab Emirates (UAE) has extradition treaties with several countries. While the specific list may change over time, countries known to have extradition treaties with the UAE include:\n\n1. **United States**\n2. **United Kingdom**\n3. **France**\n4. **India**\n5. **Saudi Arabia**\n6. **Egypt**\n7. **Italy**\n8. **Malaysia**\n9. **Spain**\n10. **Turkey**\n\nThe UAE has also signed agreements with other countries to enhance judicial cooperation, which may include provisions related to extradition. However, the specifics of these treaties, including their effectiveness and the conditions under which extradition is granted, can vary.\n\nFor the most current and detailed information, you may want to consult official government sources or legal resources that specialize in international law and extradition matters.",
